[29.516415, "o", "\u001b[?1049h\u001b[22;0;0t\u001b[?1h\u001b=\r"]
[29.53713, "o", "JOURNALCTL(1)                           journalctl                           JOURNALCTL(1)\u001b[m"]
[29.537243999999998, "o", "\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       journalctl - Print log entries from the systemd journal\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m"]
[29.537260999999997, "o", "\r\n       \u001b[1mjournalctl \u001b[22m[OPTIONS...] [MATCHES...]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mjournalctl \u001b[22mis used to print the log entries stored in the journal by \u001b[1msystemd-\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mjournald.service\u001b[22m(8) and \u001b[1msystemd-journal-remote.service\u001b[22m(8).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n"]
[29.537277999999997, "o", "       If called without parameters, it will show the contents of the journal accessible\u001b[m\r\n       to the calling user, starting with the oldest entry collected.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       If one or more match arguments are passed, the output is filtered accordingly. A\u001b[m\r\n       match is in the format \"FIELD=VALUE\", e.g.  \"_SYSTEMD_UNIT=httpd.service\",\u001b[m\r\n       referring to the components of a structured journal entry. See \u001b[1msystemd.journal-\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n"]
[29.537288, "o", "       \u001b[1mfields\u001b[22m(7) for a list of well-known fields. If multiple matches are specified\u001b[m\r\n "]
[29.537378, "o", "      matching different fields, the log entries are filtered by both, i.e. the resulting\u001b[m\r\n       output will show only entries matching all the specified matches of this kind. If\u001b[m\r\n       two matches apply to the same field, then they are automatically matched as\u001b[m\r\n       alternatives, i.e. the resulting output will show entries matching any of the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[32.537378000000004, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[32.537612, "o", "       specified matches for the same field. Finally, the character \"+\" may appear as a\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 2 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       separate word between other terms on the command line. This causes all matches\u001b[m"]
[32.540339, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 3 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       before and after to be combined in a disjunction (i.e. logical OR).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 4 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[32.560106, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 5 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       It is also possible to filter the entries by specifying an absolute file path as an\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 6 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       argument. The file path may be a file or a symbolic link and the file must exist at\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 7 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[32.587861000000004, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       the time of the query. If a file path refers to an executable binary, an \"_EXE=\"\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 8 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[32.588277, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       match for the canonicalized binary path is added to the query. If a file path\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 9 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[32.588679, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[32.588883, "o", "       refers to an executable script, a \"_COMM=\" match for the script name is added to\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 10 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[32.715859, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[32.716999, "o", "       the query. If a file path refers to a device node, \"_KERNEL_DEVICE=\" matches for\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 11 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       the kernel name of the device and for each of its ancestor devices is added to the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 12 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       query. Symbolic links are dereferenced, kernel names are synthesized, and parent\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 13 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.172643, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       devices are identified from the environment at the time of the query. In general, a\u001b[m"]
[33.173368, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 14 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.173693, "o", "       device node is the best proxy for an actual device, as log entries do not usually\u001b[m\r\n"]
[33.174381000000004, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 15 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       contain fields that identify an actual device. For the resulting log entries to be\u001b[m"]
[33.17451, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 16 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.189921, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       correct for the actual device, the relevant parts of the environment at the time\u001b[m"]
[33.190411, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 17 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       the entry was logged, in particular the actual device corresponding to the device\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 18 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.19045, "o", "       node, must have been the same as those at the time of the query. Because device\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 19 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.204178, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.204396, "o", "       nodes generally change their corresponding devices across reboots, specifying a\u001b[m"]
[33.204479, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 20 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.204536, "o", "       device node path causes the resulting entries to be restricted to those from the\u001b[m"]
[33.204593, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 21 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.204685, "o", "       current boot.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 22 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.222188, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.222517, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 23 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       Additional constraints may be added using options \u001b[1m--boot\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--unit=\u001b[22m, etc., to further\u001b[m"]
[33.222746, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 24 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.222918, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       limit what entries will be shown (logical AND).\u001b[m"]
[33.22298, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 25 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.253843, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.254126, "o", "\u001b[m"]
[33.254261, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 26 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       Output is interleaved from all accessible journal files, whether they are rotated\u001b[m"]
[33.254293000000004, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 27 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       or currently being written, and regardless of whether they belong to the system\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 28 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.285417, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.285935, "o", "       itself or are accessible user journals. The \u001b[1m--header \u001b[22moption can be used to identify\u001b[m\r\n"]
[33.286046, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 29 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.286089000000004, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.286419, "o", "       which files \u001b[4mare\u001b[24m being shown.\u001b[m"]
[33.287073, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 30 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n"]
[33.28718, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 31 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.384898, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       The set of journal files which will be used can be modified using the \u001b[1m--user\u001b[22m,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 32 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.385003, "o", "       \u001b[1m--system\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--directory\u001b[22m, and \u001b[1m--file \u001b[22moptions, see below.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 33 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.387995000000004, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n"]
[33.388067, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 34 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.656856, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.656997000000004, "o", "       All users are granted access to their private per-user journals. However, by\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 35 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.65706, "o", "       default, only root and users who are members of a few special groups are granted\u001b[m"]
[33.657084, "o", "\r\n"]
[33.657107, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 36 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.657166000000004, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.657226, "o", "       access to the system journal and the journals of other users. Members of the groups\u001b[m"]
[33.657257, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 37 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.685402, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.685667, "o", "       \"systemd-journal\", \"adm\", and \"wheel\" can read all journal files. Note that the two\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 38 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       latter groups traditionally have additional privileges specified by the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 39 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       distribution. Members of the \"wheel\" group can often perform administrative tasks.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 40 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.725105, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.725217, "o", "\u001b[m"]
[33.725253, "o", "\r\n"]
[33.72529, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 41 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[33.725541, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[33.725662, "o", "       The output is paged through \u001b[1mless \u001b[22mby default, and long lines are \"truncated\" to\u001b[m"]
[33.725772, "o", "\r\n"]
[33.726017, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 42 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       screen width. The hidden part can be viewed by using the left-arrow and right-arrow\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 43 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.337853, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       keys. Paging can be disabled; see the \u001b[1m--no-pager \u001b[22moption and the \"Environment\"\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 44 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       section below.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 45 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m"]
[34.338578, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 46 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.357722, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[34.357905, "o", "       When outputting to a tty, lines are colored according to priority: lines of level\u001b[m"]
[34.358376, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 47 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       ERROR and higher are colored red; lines of level NOTICE and higher are highlighted;\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 48 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[34.358424, "o", "       lines of level DEBUG are colored lighter grey; other lines are displayed normally.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 49 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.380309000000004, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[34.380774, "o", "\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 50 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.381370000000004, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       To write entries \u001b[4mto\u001b[24m the journal, a few methods may be used. In general, output from\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 51 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       systemd units is automatically connected to the journal, see \u001b[1msystemd-\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 52 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.416405, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1mjournald.service\u001b[22m(8). In addition, \u001b[1msystemd-cat\u001b[22m(1) may be used to send messages to\u001b[m"]
[34.416536, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 53 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       the journal directly.\u001b[m"]
[34.416619, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 54 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[34.41665, "o", "\u001b[m"]
[34.416692, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 55 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.847796, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[34.848385, "o", "\u001b[1mSOURCE OPTIONS\u001b[0m\u001b[m"]
[34.848639, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 56 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       The following options control where to read journal records from:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 57 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 58 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.868566, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1m--system\u001b[22m, \u001b[1m--user\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 59 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           Show messages from system services and the kernel (with \u001b[1m--system\u001b[22m). Show\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 60 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           messages from service of current user (with \u001b[1m--user\u001b[22m). If neither is specified,\u001b[m"]
[34.868745000000004, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 61 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.897309, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[34.897439, "o", "           show all messages that the user can see.\u001b[m"]
[34.897512, "o", "\r\n"]
[34.897596, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 62 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m"]
[34.897699, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 63 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           The \u001b[1m--user \u001b[22moption affects how \u001b[1m--unit \u001b[22marguments are treated. See \u001b[1m--unit\u001b[22m.\u001b[m"]
[34.89776, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page journalctl(1) line 64 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[34.940164, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
